textAfterTable: 14 Songs Biography Born: 03 December 1928 in Wall Lake, IA Genre: Pop Years Active: '40s, '50s, '60s, '70s, '80s, '90s, '00s, '10s An engaging crooner, TV personality, and entrepreneur, Andy Williams was one of the most bankable and popular singers of his era. With his laid-back delivery, supple voice, and amiable charm, Williams rode a wave of success that took him from a childhood vocal act with his brothers to worldwide fame as a solo artist, eventually finding latter-day success as a theater impresario in Branson, Missouri.
